ADDITIONAL DISCLAIMER — IMPORTANT, PLEASE READ

This field guide application and its species database are provided FOR
INFORMATIONAL AND EDUCATIONAL PURPOSES ONLY.

SPECIES IDENTIFICATIONS, EDIBILITY NOTES, TOXICITY WARNINGS, CONSERVATION
STATUS DESIGNATIONS, AND ALL OTHER CONTENT ARE PROVIDED "AS-IS" WITH NO
WARRANTY OF ACCURACY, COMPLETENESS, OR FITNESS FOR ANY PARTICULAR PURPOSE.

DO NOT EAT, TOUCH, OR OTHERWISE INTERACT WITH ANY PLANT, LICHEN, OR MOSS
BASED SOLELY ON INFORMATION IN THIS GUIDE. Misidentification of wild plants
can cause serious injury or death.

ANY ACTION TAKEN OR NOT TAKEN BASED ON INFORMATION IN THIS GUIDE IS SOLELY
AT THE USER'S OWN RISK. The author and contributors assume no liability
whatsoever for any damages, injuries, or losses arising from direct or
indirect use of this guide, including but not limited to:

  - Misidentification of species
  - Reliance on edibility, toxicity, or safety information
  - Decisions regarding land management, conservation, or restoration
  - Medical or allergic reactions from plant contact or ingestion
  - Property damage from invasive species management decisions

This guide is NOT a substitute for:
  - Professional botanical identification by a qualified expert
  - Medical advice from a licensed healthcare provider
  - Land management guidance from certified professionals
  - Legal advice regarding protected species or regulations

Always consult multiple authoritative sources and qualified professionals
before making any identification-dependent decisions. When in doubt about
a species identification, DO NOT interact with the organism.

Cal-IPC (California Invasive Plant Council) ratings included in this guide
are sourced from the Cal-IPC Inventory (cal-ipc.org) and are subject to
periodic revision. Verify current ratings at cal-ipc.org.

Conservation status designations (CNPS rare plant ranks, federal/state
listings) are subject to change. Verify current status with the California
Natural Diversity Database (CNDDB) and the CNPS Rare Plant Inventory.

