PHOTO AND DATA ATTRIBUTION

Species photographs are fetched from iNaturalist (inaturalist.org) via the
taxa/autocomplete API and are subject to their respective Creative Commons
licenses as set by individual photographers. This application does not store
or redistribute photographs; they are loaded dynamically from iNaturalist's
servers.

Species data in this guide was compiled from the following public sources:

  - Muns, B. & Chester, T. Santa Monica Mountains Flora: A Checklist of
    the Vascular Plants (1983, rev. 1999, updated 2002)
  - Chester, T., Fisher, R., Strong, J. et al. Flora of Lower Eaton
    Canyon, San Gabriel Mountains (2003)
  - Muns, B. Flora of Chantry Flat / Santa Anita Canyon (1999)
  - Raven, P.H., Thompson, H.J. & Prigge, B.A. Flora of the Santa
    Monica Mountains, California (2nd ed., 1986)
  - Cooper, D.S. Flora of Griffith Park, Los Angeles, California (2015)
  - Tucker, S.C. & Ryan, B.D. Revised Catalog of Lichens, Lichenicoles,
    and Allied Fungi in California. Constancea 84/85 (2006/2013)
  - Malcolm, B., Shevock, J. & Norris, D. California Mosses (2009)
  - Sholars, T. Lupines of California (CNPS Press)
  - Strong, J. & Chester, T. Geographic Distribution of Arctostaphylos
    Species in the San Gabriel Mountains
  - California Native Plant Society (CNPS) Inventory of Rare and
    Endangered Plants
  - Cal-IPC. California Invasive Plant Inventory (2006-2024)
  - Calflora (calflora.org)
  - Jepson eFlora (ucjeps.berkeley.edu)
  - iNaturalist observation data (inaturalist.org)
  - Theodore Payne Foundation Native Plant Database
  - Las Pilitas Nursery Native Plant Reference
  - Xerces Society California Pollinator Plant List

Map data: Esri, iNaturalist
Observation data: iNaturalist API (place_id=962, Los Angeles County)

